4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH AND CELEBRATING THE LIFE AND
5 LEGACY OF JOHN HACKETT, JR.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that we note the
8 passing of John Hackett, Jr. of Birmingham, Alabama, on
9 February 23, 2026, while we also celebrate his long,
10 accomplished life that ended at the age of 82; and
11 WHEREAS, John was a proud alumnus, dedicated leader,
12 and longtime District 7 member of the Alabama A&M University
13 (AAMU) Board of Trustees; his departure leaves a void in the
14 lives of his loving family, many friends, and the community
15 where he was highly regarded; and
16 WHEREAS, born in Birmingham on January 17, 1944, John
17 was a 1965 graduate of AAMU, earning a Bachelor's degree in
18 Building Construction Engineering; he often spoke fondly of
19 his student days on "The Hill," reflecting a lifelong love
20 for his alma mater and its mission; and
21 WHEREAS, John served as President of the AAMU
22 National Alumni Association from 2012 to 2014, helping to
23 strengthen alumni engagement and support for the
24 institution; his leadership was marked by humility,
25 dedication, and an unwavering commitment to advancing the
26 University's future; and
27 WHEREAS, professionally, John was CEO of J.H. Jr. &
28 Associates, LLC; he began his career teaching woodworking in
Page 1

Associates, LLC; he began his career teaching woodworking in
HR183 INTRODUCED
29 the Birmingham and Vestavia school systems for approximately
30 seven years before embarking on more than 35 years of
31 service with the City of Birmingham, the Housing Authority
32 of the Birmingham District, and Alabama Power Company;
33 throughout his career, he held various leadership roles and
34 developed expertise in planning, maintenance management,
35 construction, purchasing, inventory management, warehousing,
36 and administration; and
37 WHEREAS, John pursued additional professional
38 certifications in park and recreation maintenance management
39 and master maintenance management from North Carolina State
40 University, and he completed maintenance management
41 certifications at The University of Alabama; and
42 WHEREAS, John was a member of the Alpha Phi Chapter
43 of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Incorporated, and remained
44 active in civic and community life; he and his wife of
45 nearly 45 years, the former Lila Morgan, built a legacy
46 rooted in faith, family, and service; in addition to his
47 beloved wife, he is survived by four children, seven
48 grandchildren, and five great-grandchildren; and
49 WHEREAS, the influence of John Hackett will live on
50 through the countless lives he shaped; now therefore,
51 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
52 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of John Hackett, Jr.
53 is recorded with deep sadness, and this resolution is
54 offered in tribute to his life and service to others, along
55 with heartfelt sympathy to his family, whose grief is shared
56 by many.
